            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1654,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Uv7WUcxN1WFeypxwcMfsTT\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** (also called \\\"Details\\\") are the text lines that appear **below your headlines** in your Google Ads.\\n\\nHere's what you need to know about them:\\n\\n**Key Details:**\\n- **Length limit:** Each description can be up to **90 characters** (strict Google limit)\\n- **How many show:** Google typically displays **up to 2 descriptions** in a single ad\\n- **Purpose:** They give you space to expand on your value proposition and explain:\\n  - Benefits of your service\\n  - Features you offer\\n  - Calls to action (like \\\"Get a quote\\\" or \\\"Learn more\\\")\\n  - Social proof or special offers\\n\\n**Example for your scheduling tool:**\\n- **Headline:** \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\"\\n- **Description:** \\\"Connect calendars, skip the back-and-forth. Trusted by 2,000+ teams.\\\"\\n\\nDescriptions work together with your headlines to tell a complete story and convince people to click your ad. Since Google mixes and matches them, you want to create descriptions that work well independently AND complement different headline combinations.\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some descriptions for your scheduling tool campaign? I can create 4 compelling options that highlight your key benefits and include strong calls-to-action!\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2579,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":281,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
