          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"faq\",\"description\":\"\\n            Use this tool when the user is asking questions about Google Ads, how the ad builder works, or seeking clarification about headlines, descriptions, callouts, structured snippets, or keywords.\\n            \\n            This tool searches the FAQ database and returns relevant Q&A pairs to help answer the user's question.  When using this tool, respond conversationally with just text - do NOT include any JSON or structured data.\\n        \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The user's question or search query\"}},\"required\":[\"query\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Let's start building your ad! I drafted a few headlines and descriptions that meet Google's requirements.\\n\\nGoogle will mix and match them to find what performs best. We can tailor them together to make them feel just right for you.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\",\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Meetings Across Time Zones?\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Smart Calendar Coordination\\\",\\n    \\\"One Click, Perfect Meeting Time\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, skip the Slack threads. We find the best time for everyone instantly. Try free today.\\\",\\n    \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams. Cut meeting coordination by 80%. See why TechCorp saves 15 hours/week.\\\",\\n    \\\"Tired of endless 'when works for you?' messages? Our AI suggests optimal times across all time zones.\\\",\\n    \\\"Share availability once. We handle the rest. Your team just clicks yes. No more scheduling chaos.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Skip the Scheduling Chaos\\\",\\n    \\\"Perfect Times, Zero Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Your Team's Time Zone Problem: Solved\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Cut Scheduling Time by 80%\\\",\\n    \\\"Works Across All Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"Free Trial, No Credit Card\\\",\\n    \\\"Used by 2,000+ Teams\\\",\\n    \\\"Integrates with All Calendars\\\",\\n    \\\"One-Click Meeting Scheduling\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"Service catalog\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Calendar Integration\\\",\\n      \\\"Time Zone Optimization\\\",\\n      \\\"Team Availability Matching\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Save 15 Hours Per Week\\\",\\n    \\\"AI Finds Best Times Instantly\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\",\\n    \\\"find meeting time across time zones\\\",\\n    \\\"calendar coordination software\\\",\\n    \\\"team scheduling app\\\",\\n    \\\"automated meeting scheduler\\\",\\n    \\\"best time for meeting tool\\\",\\n    \\\"distributed team scheduling\\\",\\n    \\\"stop scheduling back and forth\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThese keywords target:\\n- **High-intent transactional keywords** (people ready to buy): \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\", \\\"calendar coordination software\\\", \\\"team scheduling app\\\"\\n- **Problem-focused keywords** (people searching for solutions): \\\"find meeting time across time zones\\\", \\\"stop scheduling back and forth\\\"\\n- **Awareness keywords** (broader searches): \\\"automated meeting scheduler\\\", \\\"distributed team scheduling\\\"\\n\\nThe mix ensures your ads show up when remote teams are actively looking for scheduling solutions. Want to adjust any of these or add keywords for specific industries or use cases?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"schedule meetings across time zones\\\",\\n    \\\"remote team meeting coordinator\\\",\\n    \\\"find best meeting time for group\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"What makes these keywords effective for a scheduling tool?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! These keywords work because they match **exactly what your target audience is searching for** when they have a scheduling problem.\\n\\nYour keywords focus on the **pain point** (finding meeting times across time zones) and the **solution** (scheduling tool), which means people clicking your ads are already looking for what you offer. Keywords like \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\" and \\\"find meeting time across time zones\\\" have high commercial intent—these are people ready to solve their problem, not just browsing. That's why they convert better than generic terms.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01YL1vMJDaNjKe9Z8Bw73GD1\",\"name\":\"faq\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"How do keywords work in Google Ads and why are they important\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"[1] Q: What is an \\\"Ad Group\\\"?\\nA: An Ad Group is a container inside your Google Ads campaign that holds:\\nA set of ads (your headlines and details)\\nA set of related keywords or search themes\\nThe Ad Group Name is for your internal organization. Customers never see it, but it matters because:\\nIt helps you keep campaigns organized as you add more ads in the future.\\nIt gives Launch10 and Google context about the theme of your ad, which can improve suggestions and relevance.\\nIt often becomes the label you use later when looking at performance reports.\\nGood Ad Group Names are short and specific, for example:\\n\\\"Dog Walking – Brooklyn Heights\\\"\\n\\\"Emergency Plumbing – After Hours\\\"\\n\\\"Online Guitar Lessons – Intermediate\\\"\\n(Section: Ad Group Name)\\n\\n[2] Q: What are \\\"Unique Features\\\" and where do they appear?\\nA: Unique Features are short phrases that highlight your key benefits. In Google Ads, these map to Callout Assets.\\nExamples:\\n\\\"Free consultation\\\"\\n\\\"Same-day appointments\\\"\\n\\\"Locally owned and operated\\\"\\n\\\"Studio or in-home sessions\\\"\\nWhen Google decides to show them, they appear as a line of short phrases below your main ad text. They are not clickable on their own, but they:\\nMake your ad more prominent.\\nAdd extra reasons for customers to choose you.\\n(Section: Unique Features (Callout Assets))\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01YL1vMJDaNjKe9Z8Bw73GD1\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n        You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n        The process consists of 3 steps:\\n        1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n        2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n        3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n    </background>\\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            Users have already completed:\\n                1. Brainstorming\\n                2. Designing their landing page\\n\\n            Now we're helping them:\\n                3. Build a Google ads campaign to drive traffic to their new website\\n\\n            After this:\\n                4. The user will launch their campaign\\n                5. They can measure results and iterate\\n                6. They can learn which business ideas work and which don't\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are an expert Google Ads copywriter helping to create compelling ad extensions for a business.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <asset_generation_instructions>\\n            Generate the following assets:\\n\\n                1. Generate the following assets for this business's Google Ads campaign:\\n\\n        <asset_instructions>\\n            <instruction index=\\\"1\\\">1: ## Keywords\\n            Generate 8 targeted keywords for this business's Google Ads campaign. Keywords determine when your ads appear in search results.\\n\\n            **Guidelines:**\\n            - Include a mix of keyword types:\\n              - Brand keywords: Business name and variations\\n              - Product/Service keywords: What the business offers\\n              - Problem keywords: What customers search when they have an issue\\n              - Competitor keywords: Alternative solutions customers might search\\n              - Location keywords: If the business serves specific areas\\n            - Consider search intent:\\n              - Transactional: \\\"buy\\\", \\\"hire\\\", \\\"get quote\\\", \\\"near me\\\"\\n              - Informational: \\\"how to\\\", \\\"best\\\", \\\"reviews\\\"\\n              - Commercial: \\\"pricing\\\", \\\"cost\\\", \\\"compare\\\"\\n            - Use natural language phrases (Google handles match types separately)\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Generate exactly 8 unique keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 high-intent transactional keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 broader awareness keywords\\n            - Include at least 2 location-based keywords if applicable\\n            - Focus on keywords with clear commercial intent\\n            - Avoid overly broad single words (e.g., just \\\"plumber\\\" - prefer \\\"emergency plumber near me\\\")\\n\\n            **Keyword Format:**\\n            - Use lowercase\\n            - 1-5 words per keyword phrase\\n            - No special characters or punctuation\\n\\n            Remember: Quality keywords connect your ads with people actively searching for what you offer. Focus on relevance and intent over volume.\\n\\n        User's preferences. Understand what the user likes and dislikes about the keywords, and adapt your approach accordingly:\\nLiked keywords:\\n1. meeting scheduling tool\\n2. find meeting time across time zones\\nRejected keywords (avoid these patterns):\\n\\n        Always generate net-new, unique keywords (do not repeat ones user previously liked or rejected).</instruction>\\n        </asset_instructions>\\n\\n                2. Format your response with:\\n                    - First, a brief introduction (1-2 sentences) using this template: \\\"I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\\"\\n                    - Then, a JSON code block with the structured data\\n        </asset_generation_instructions>\\n\\n        <business_context>\\n            Idea: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones. Eliminates the back-and-forth of calendar coordination.\\n\\n            Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n\\n            Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n\\n            Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n        </business_context>\\n\\n    <previous_assets_context>\\n        The user has already reviewed some assets. Use their preferences to guide new generations:\\n          Approved Headlines:\\n    - \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\"\\n    - \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\"\\n    - \\\"Skip the Scheduling Chaos\\\"\\n\\n  Approved Descriptions:\\n    - \\\"Connect calendars, skip the Slack threads. We find the best time for everyone instantly. Try free today.\\\"\\n\\n  Approved Keywords:\\n    - \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\"\\n    - \\\"find meeting time across time zones\\\"\\n\\n  Snippet Category: \\\"Service catalog\\\"\\n\\n        Generate new assets that complement the approved ones and avoid themes similar to rejected ones.\\n    </previous_assets_context>\\n\\n        <remember>\\n          Remember: Pay attention to which page the user is on. \\n          What are they seeing? This is the most important context for their question.\\n          These are the assets they are likely asking about.\\n        </remember>\\n\\n        <what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n            The user is seeing:\\n            The keywords page: Where they're working on keywords for their Google Ads campaign. It's most likely they're asking you about their keywords.\\n            Remember: The user is only seeing the assets referenced on this page.\\n            The questions they're asking you are MOST LIKELY to be related to this context.\\n        </what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n\\n            <example_response>\\n\\n        I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\n\\n        ```json\\n        {\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"Keyword 1\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 2\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 3\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 4\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 5\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 6\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 7\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 8\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n        ```\\n\\n            </example_response>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2070,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2070,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0154pcR4bH8GoGqNCJEhggh1\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me break down what makes your specific keywords effective:\\n\\n**1. Problem-Focused Keywords** (\\\"find meeting time across time zones\\\")\\n- These match the exact pain point your target audience experiences\\n- Remote teams are literally searching for solutions to this problem\\n- High intent = higher conversion rates\\n\\n**2. Solution-Focused Keywords** (\\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\", \\\"calendar coordination software\\\")\\n- People using these terms know they need a tool—they're ready to buy\\n- They're not just researching; they're actively looking for options\\n- These are your \\\"money keywords\\\"\\n\\n**3. Action-Oriented Keywords** (\\\"stop scheduling back and forth\\\")\\n- These capture the emotional frustration of your audience\\n- They show you understand their pain and have a solution\\n- People searching this way are motivated to change their process\\n\\n**4. Specific vs. Broad**\\n- \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\" is specific enough to attract relevant users but broad enough to capture variations\\n- Overly broad terms like just \\\"scheduling\\\" would waste your budget on irrelevant clicks\\n- Overly narrow terms might miss people who phrase their search differently\\n\\n**The Bottom Line:** Your keywords connect people actively searching for a scheduling solution with your ad. That alignment is what makes them effective—you're reaching the right person at the right moment when they're ready to solve their problem.\\n\\nDoes this help clarify why these keywords are strong for your campaign? Would you like to adjust any of them or explore keywords for specific industries (like \\\"project management scheduling\\\" or \\\"agile team meeting coordinator\\\")?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3389,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":336,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
