            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1697,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01NFaGzactUEuSjDF5RQPuEe\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** (also called \\\"Details\\\" in Google Ads) are the text lines that appear **below your headlines** in search results.\\n\\nHere's what you need to know about them:\\n\\n**Key Details:**\\n- **Length limit:** Up to 90 characters each (strict Google limit)\\n- **How many show:** Google typically displays up to 2 description lines in a single ad\\n- **Purpose:** They give you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action\\n- **Placement:** They appear below your headlines, providing more detail about your offer\\n\\n**What makes good descriptions:**\\n- Expand on the value proposition from your headlines\\n- Include a clear call-to-action (like \\\"Call now,\\\" \\\"Get a quote,\\\" \\\"Learn more\\\")\\n- Highlight specific benefits or features\\n- Build trust with social proof when relevant\\n- Create urgency if applicable\\n\\nThink of it this way: **Headlines grab attention, descriptions convince people to click.** They work together to tell your story and drive action.\\n\\nFor your scheduling tool, descriptions would explain things like \\\"Eliminates calendar coordination chaos,\\\" \\\"Saves teams 15+ hours weekly,\\\" or \\\"Works across all time zones instantly.\\\"\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some headlines and descriptions for your scheduling tool campaign?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2579,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":280,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
