        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1484,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1484,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01V8Xt2E8yk1S3UD8a8z89zf\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Yes, you can see your headlines in the preview! \\n\\nAt the top of the page, there's an **Ad Preview card** that updates as you edit your headlines and descriptions. It shows you a sample combination of your content so you can visualize how your ad will look and check for things like typos, tone, and messaging.\\n\\nA couple of things to keep in mind:\\n\\n1. **It's a sample, not all variations** — The preview shows one possible combination of your headlines and descriptions, but Google will mix and match them in different ways. Different customers may see different combinations than what's shown in the preview.\\n\\n2. **It helps you visualize** — The preview is mainly there to help you see how your ad looks and feels, not to show every possible version Google might display.\\n\\nSo as you refine your headlines, keep an eye on that preview to make sure the messaging feels right and everything looks good! Would you like me to generate some headlines and descriptions for your scheduling tool, or would you like to adjust any that I've already created?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2590,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":229,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
